<item>
            <title>[LU-20082] LNet: TCP receive buffer size setting not taking effect.</title>
                <link>https://jira.whamcloud.com/browse/LU-20082</link>
                <project id="10000" key="LU">Lustre</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;When using the &lt;b&gt;lnet_sock_setbuf&lt;/b&gt; function to set &lt;b&gt;txbufsize&lt;/b&gt; and &lt;b&gt;rxbufsize&lt;/b&gt;, there is an issue: &lt;b&gt;rxbufsize&lt;/b&gt; is incorrectly assigned to &lt;b&gt;sk-&amp;gt;sk_sndbuf&lt;/b&gt;. This causes both &lt;b&gt;sk_sndbuf&lt;/b&gt; and &lt;b&gt;sk_rcvbuf&lt;/b&gt; to behave unexpectedly.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;This issue was introduced during the refactoring to support kernel 5.8 due to kernel interface changes. Refer to &lt;a href=&quot;https://jira.whamcloud.com/browse/LU-13783&quot; title=&quot;Support for linux kernel version 5.8&quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;LU-13783&quot;&gt;&lt;del&gt;LU-13783&lt;/del&gt;&lt;/a&gt;.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Code:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;div class=&quot;code panel&quot; style=&quot;border-width: 1px;&quot;&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;codeContent panelContent&quot;&gt;
&lt;pre class=&quot;code-java&quot;&gt;
void
lnet_sock_setbuf(struct socket *sock, &lt;span class=&quot;code-object&quot;&gt;int&lt;/span&gt; txbufsize, &lt;span class=&quot;code-object&quot;&gt;int&lt;/span&gt; rxbufsize)
{
&#160; &#160; &#160; &#160; struct sock *sk = sock-&amp;gt;sk;

&#160; &#160; &#160; &#160; &lt;span class=&quot;code-keyword&quot;&gt;if&lt;/span&gt; (txbufsize != 0) {
&#160; &#160; &#160; &#160; &#160; &#160; &#160; &#160; sk-&amp;gt;sk_userlocks |= SOCK_SNDBUF_LOCK;
&#160; &#160; &#160; &#160; &#160; &#160; &#160; &#160; sk-&amp;gt;sk_sndbuf = txbufsize;
&#160; &#160; &#160; &#160; &#160; &#160; &#160; &#160; sk-&amp;gt;sk_write_space(sk);
&#160; &#160; &#160; &#160; }

&#160; &#160; &#160; &#160; &lt;span class=&quot;code-keyword&quot;&gt;if&lt;/span&gt; (rxbufsize != 0) {
&#160; &#160; &#160; &#160; &#160; &#160; &#160; &#160; sk-&amp;gt;sk_userlocks |= SOCK_RCVBUF_LOCK;
&#160; &#160; &#160; &#160; &#160; &#160; &#160; &#160; sk-&amp;gt;sk_sndbuf = rxbufsize;
&#160; &#160; &#160; &#160; }
}&lt;/pre&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;
&lt;p&gt;`&lt;b&gt;sk-&amp;gt;sk_sndbuf = rxbufsize&lt;/b&gt;` should be `&lt;b&gt;sk-&amp;gt;sk_rcvbuf = rxbufsize&lt;/b&gt;`.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&#160;&lt;/p&gt;</description>
